OL,3,CUK urged to rein in spending as debt
OL,4,Cspirals beyond other developed
OL,5,Ceconomies
OL,7,FThe International Monetary Fund (IMF)
OL,8,Fhas repeated its warning that the
OL,9,Ffinances of the UK government cannot
OL,10,Fbe sustained without either cuts to
OL,11,Fthe scope of the welfare state or
OL,12,Fincreases in taxes.
OL,14,F"The global battle against inflation
OL,15,Fhas largely been won," Pierre-Olivier
OL,16,FGourinchas, the IMF's Economic
OL,17,FController in World Economic Outlook,
OL,18,Fsaid.
