OL,3,CUK urged to rein in spending as debt
OL,4,Cspirals beyond other developed
OL,5,Ceconomies
OL,7,FThe IMF's figures show that the ratio
OL,8,Fbetween government debt and gross
OL,9,Fdomestic product (GDP) - an important
OL,10,Findicator of a country's economic
OL,11,Fhealth - has risen by 57 percentage
OL,12,Fpoints in the UK in the last 20 years.
OL,14,FThat's a bigger increase than in the
OL,15,FUnited States (49), Greece and Spain
OL,16,F(both 56), plus Portugal (37) -
OL,17,Fcountries we perhaps like to think of
OL,18,Fas being in a worse economic shape
OL,19,Fthan the UK.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
