OL,4,Cspirals beyond other developed
OL,5,Ceconomies
OL,7,FShe spent the election campaign in
OL,8,FJune insisting the only taxes that
OL,9,Fwould rise under a Labour government
OL,10,Fwere those set out in the party's
OL,11,Fmanifesto.
OL,13,FAfter becoming Chancellor, she
OL,14,Fannounced that she had discovered
OL,15,Fthings were in a much worse state than
OL,16,Fshe had previously thought, and that
OL,17,Fadditional tax rises and spending cuts
OL,18,Fwould be necessary.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
