OL,3,CUK urged to rein in spending as debt
OL,4,Cspirals beyond other developed
OL,5,Ceconomies
OL,7,FIn April, the IMF named the UK as one
OL,8,Fof four countries which urgently
OL,9,Fneeded to take steps "to address
OL,10,Ffundamental imbalances between
OL,11,Fspending and revenues".
OL,13,FThe following month, on a visit to the
OL,14,FUK, the IMF said the government's
OL,15,Fspending plans beyond April 2025 are
OL,16,Funrealistically low and that whoever
OL,17,Fwon the election would need to either
OL,18,Fraise taxes by between #22 billion and
OL,19,F#39 billion a year or find equivalent
OL,20,Fsavings to get debt under control.
