OL,7,FAdding that whoever won the election
OL,8,Fwould probably need either to raise
OL,9,F#30 billion a year more by raising
OL,10,Ftaxes or spending would need to be
OL,11,Freduced by a similar amount.
OL,13,FThe IMF even recommended ways in which
OL,14,Fthe hole could be filled, including
OL,15,Fscrapping the triple-Lock on pensions,
OL,16,Fbroadening the bases for VAT and
OL,17,Finheritance tax, also reforming
OL,18,Fcapital gains and property taxation.
